   Scholarship Scams (US Federal Trade Commission)
   http://www.ftc.gov/bcp/conline/edcams/scholarship/index.html
   Need money for college? Unfortunately, in their efforts to pay the
   bills, many students and their families are falling prey to scholarship
   scams. The Federal Trade Commission cautions students on how to
   discover fraud.
   Related Topics: Parents  Scholarships and grants  Consumer rights
   __________________________________________________________________


                                 Three Stars
                               # Ratings:  24
                               # Visits:  421

   Savings Bonds for Education (US Dept of the Treasury)
   http://www.publicdebt.treas.gov/sav/saveduca.htm
   Learn about the "Education Bond Program", which allows US savings bond
   interest to be excluded from Federal income tax the year that the bonds
   are redeemed to pay qualified higher education expenses. Great
   information and links!
   Related Topics: Parents  Scholarships and grants  Student loans  State
   financial aid  Taxes

